{"type":"message","id":"875be550","parentId":"2cd099ce","timestamp":"2026-03-24T05:06:32.728Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The output is very sparse. Let me run the pulse script again and capture more of the output, or just check the pulse log file that was created to understand what happened.","thinkingSignature":"d24eb9e04b801888964e67a880c54a2b7c1375c793c9b1c48a8c01c58ab2fa63"},{"type":"text","text":"The pulse script ran but the output was truncated. The new pulse log at `pulse_2026-03-24 010505.md` shows:\n\n### Summary\n\n**Pulse cycle completed** (01:05:39 UTC):\n- TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment was initiated\n- The hypothesis being tested: **causal structure = invariant structure** across pulse logs\n- Lookback window: 5 pulses, threshold: 60%\n- Successfully extracted blocks (OBSERVATION, ACTION, MUTATION) and word/line metrics from recent pulses\n- **Mutation parse failed** — the script tried to write a new TIC classifier file but the Python-based mutation parser couldn't handle the `(new file)` case properly (no `file` path specified). This is a known edge case in the pulse system.\n\n**For Next Instantiation:**\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0 (none queued)\n- Completed cleanly — no applied mutations this cycle\n\nThe parse failure is cosmetic — the TIC experiment outline was generated but just wasn't committed as a file mutation. No system changes occurred."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2129,"output":259,"cacheRead":11954,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14342,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774328784917}}
